reviews.review: The acting was great as always but the story didn't seem to take much from the previous two movies. The villain also made absolutely no sense... for those of you who haven't seen the movie yet, just wait and see.

I almost fell asleep on three different occasions. First scene with Rey is a hard eye roll. I love the recons, I love the adventure when the main characters are together, but there all consequences have been removed. The number of character death psychs is excessive. The amount of convenience, luck, and things that just magically work just makes the movie boring. I liked about 20% of the movie. 50% could be removed and you wouldn't miss anything. 30% was wtf moments.

I was absorbed into seeing how this trilogy would wrap up and how it was not going to please everyone. Itâ€™s something that will certainly open up the conversation on what more can drive Star Wars for the next installments.

It was a tie up movie. I've never really established a relationship with any of the characters, but that is somewhat common with many of the star wars characters. Character development has been superficial since the originals.

Very entertaining and a roller coaster of a ride. I can see why the critics are split as this is a fans film and is very different to the Last Jedi (which I loved and without the Canto Bight detour was close behind Episodes V and IV for me).

The stand outs for me are all the scenes with Daisy Ridley and Adam Driver. Amazing chemistry and fantastic lightsaber duels.

If you haven't watched Rebels I would recommend watching some before you go like season 2 Twlight of the Apprentice and season 4 World between worlds.
This does not fit in with the original trilogy, retcons several items, the method to beating the main villain is terrible, and it breaks the whole series.  It is unbelievably bad to the lore.
As a big fan of star wars i think this is one of the best star wars movies! that movie was fun and it ended the saga in a great way. it's full of action.the story is also great.9/10
It was too long.  Could have been 30-40 minutes shorter
It had to come to end, so I would recommend seeing.
Well done movie overall. However, there are lots of gaps and open ends in the story line, which are covered up by the action but don't really make sense once you think about it afterwards.
